Flowering branches slightly longer-spined and narrower than sterile branches. Faint white annual growth-marks on the dark green surfaces of some stems. Flowers and fruits are from the distal 1 to 4 dm of the stems. Fruit not eaten by the residents, green and fuzzy outside, pure white inside; floral remnant persistent. Bruises and cut surfaces redden immediately and blacken in minutes. Pith and cortex firm and not visibly mucilaginous.
